    "recipeIngredient": [
        "1 1/4 cups packed light brown sugar ",
        "3/4 cup granulated sugar ",
        "1 cup (8 oz.) unsalted butter, at room temperature ",
        "2 large eggs",
        "2 tsp. vanilla extract",
        "2 1/2 cups (about 10 5/8 oz.) all-purpose flour ",
        "1 1/2 tsp. kosher salt",
        "1 tsp. baking soda",
        "1 1/2 cups uncooked quick-cooking oats",
        "1 1/2 cups (9 oz.) milk chocolate chips (from 1 [12-oz.] pkg.)",
        "2/3 cup (4 oz.) toffee bits (such as Bits of Brickle) (from 1 [8-oz.] pkg.)",
        "2/3 cup (5 1/2 oz.) mini candy-coated milk chocolate pieces (such as M&amp;M’S)"
    ],
    "recipeInstructions": [
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/x_FP_QWrFWtqNa5WSjuQaZMb3pY=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Monster_Cookies_002-758c11e648fd47ce991720cb2ceb27bb.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Prepare oven and baking sheets: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line 2 large rimmed baking sheets with parchment paper."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/bnSuQNC1p8OZFVjHhKdGxP5cwbI=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Monster_Cookies_003-10523b2bd681404894a825c03f5e1002.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Cream butter and sugar: Beat together brown sugar, granulated sugar, and butter in the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment on medium speed until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes, scraping down sides of bowl as needed. "
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/j1P5nNmMoEgfQsKw0ttvYidUwCc=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Monster_Cookies_004-f8bfb8a2c2a441a6bff8a0eaf0366530.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Add eggs: Add eggs and vanilla; continue beating on medium speed until just combined, about 30 seconds."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/j8ZruS2SQMZGqYpbp9FcDbu9FZE=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Monster_Cookies_005-16d4706ba5ee4c45ab3e075d50ce7038.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Combine and add dry ingredients: Whisk together flour, salt, and baking soda in a medium bowl. Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture, beating on low speed until fully incorporated, 1 to 2 minutes, scraping down sides of bowl as needed."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/CEusgGqm_c2sXIa1TQ2pOcQqXjs=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Monster_Cookies_006-d8b58935fb73456db129a7510a4b2572.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Add oats and candies: Add oats, chocolate chips, toffee bits, and mini candy-coated chocolate pieces; beat on low speed until just combined, 30 to 45 seconds."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/5W0HWkUY-GjsXxfmIz5zHAvIbSQ=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Monster_Cookies_007-81cfdfa32ff041c19b3a01cd4c73726f.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Scoop cookie dough: Scoop half of dough using a 2 1/2-tablespoon (1 1/2-oz.) scoop, and place on prepared baking sheets about 2 inches apart (about 8 cookies per baking sheet). Cover remaining dough with plastic wrap, and set aside at room temperature until ready to use. "
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/YVF8by6kag2LwYK6GsMsWohSHsU=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Monster_Cookies_008-378325da7b0e4f3aa5bb5abda0356004.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Bake cookies: Bake cookies in preheated oven until edges are slightly golden brown and set, 16 to 18 minutes, rotating baking sheets halfway through bake time."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "image": [
                {
                    "@type": "ImageObject",
                    "url": "https://www.southernliving.com/thmb/WzSokl1J18PnwkIV-xczG_HCufg=/1500x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/Monster_Cookies_009-833ee87a97014d4abc7ecc48381a2f96.jpg"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Cool cookies: Cool cookies on baking sheets 5 minutes; transfer cookies to a wire rack to cool completely, about 20 minutes. Repeat procedure with remaining cookie dough."
        }
    ],
